OL,4,CInfected Blood Inquiry findings
OL,6,F30,000 people were infected with
OL,7,Fcontaminated blood in the 70's and
OL,8,F80's. A public inquiry into the
OL,9,Fscandal will report its findings on
OL,10,FMonday.
OL,12,FBob Strachan added: "First and
OL,13,Fforemost, there has to be an admission
OL,14,Fof guilt and apology made.
OL,16,F"You know, obviously they can't make
OL,17,Frestitution for the lives that have
OL,18,Fbeen lost or things like that. But
OL,19,Fthere has to be accountability, first
OL,20,Fand foremost is the bare minimum.
